description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse – General Surgical Unit (Hunter/Lister ward and Surgical Assessment Unit)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**We offer full-time and part-time working hours.**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The General Surgical Unit was the first unit within the trust to achieve the award of ward accreditation, which is a standard for consistently providing an excellent standard of patient care and staff support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit has 40 inpatient beds, and cares for emergency surgical patients, with colorectal, upper gastrointestinal, urological and intestinal failure conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within the Unit we also have Surgical Assessment Unit open 24 hours a day seeing a variety of different emergency surgical patients, within a unit consisting of 6 trolleys and 6 chairs. The unit takes referrals from GP surgeries, Emergency department, Clinical Nurse Specialists and direct from post-discharge patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are also in the process of developing a Surgical Higher Monitoring Unit within the unit which will offer the successful candidate several opportunities to learn, develop and train.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post includes a rotation between all departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to be involved in innovation and change in a purpose built environment. We are looking for highly motivated Staff Nurses who enjoy a fast-paced, supported working environment and have an interest in acute abdominal surgery. Within the unit we work closely with the surgical team to provide gold standard care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a strong team of senior nurses to help mentor and guide new nurses as well as providing external education opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a wide range of shifts with flexible working arrangements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also encourage personal and professional development, with opportunities to progress within the trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a wide range of in-house development as well as supporting external education opportunities and in department rotations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Managers Samantha Harman / Claire Thatcher on 0118 322 7987 or samantha.harman@royalberkshire.nhs.uk / claire.thatcher@royalberkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
